history.text: Hi! Have you seen the movie "John Wick?" I wanted to talk with you about it!
I have seen the movie
I think it was really good! Keanu Reeves definitely did a great job acting in it.
I agree, the role definitely suited him.
It made me sad when they killed his dog, though.
I hated seeing the little beagle die, it was almost too much.
I am surprised that the movie only got a "B" score. I would watch it again. Would you?
I totally would, in fact, I bought the Blu-Ray
Do you like action movies like this one?
I absolutely do. This is my favorite genre of film.
What about you?
I had forgotten how John Wick's nickname was "Baba Yaga." Do you know what that means?
I also am a big action film fan!
If I remember correctly, it meant something like the boogeyman, right?
I think you are right! Remember when the father figured out his son had stolen Wick's car and killed his dog? His facial expression of terror and anger were well-acted.
oh yeah, he knew that things were about to get real
That nightclub at the end of the movie was pretty cool!
"the Red Circle"
Yep, it was really cool, and John Wick tore it to pieces. That made it even cooler
I agree! What did you think about the hotel that Wick stayed at, and how Ms. Perkins tried to sneak in and kill him?
I kind of saw that coming, but it was still an interesting part of the movie. She got hers in the end.
I thought the method of payment (i.e., those gold coins) was interesting.
Yeah, it showed these people as being part of a secret society
What did you think about the ending of the movie where John takes the puppy that was supposed to be euthanized and goes to the boardwalk?
I think it was a good ending, the puppy was very similar in circumstances to himself
Plus I have a soft spot for bully breeds. :)
I agree! I love dogs. What do you think about the actor who played Viggo?
He was a great actor, it is unfortunate that he recently passed away in real life.
I did not know that! So, what would you rate the movie?
Definitely better than a B, at least A- to me
I definitely agree! I would  have said A- to A.
These types of films are just never given high ratings by critics, for whatever reason.

The critical responses to the movie didn't seem to warrant the rating the critic's gave it. There was no definite criticism, but rather a certain applaud to Reeves for reentering the genre in a positive way.
That was what I noticed as well.
